Hanno BÃ¶ck discovered that Bind incorrectly handled certain malformed keys
when configured to perform DNSSEC validation. A remote attacker could use

title: Bind vulnerability
action: In general, a standard system update will make all the necessary changes.
isummary:
Bind could be made to crash if it received specially crafted network
traffic.
